And I'd seen the same thing.

01:36:21.000 --> 01:36:25.000
I turned out I got the local papers and the Atlanta Constitution.

01:36:25.000 --> 01:36:31.000
They were, a story was moving across the Constitution,

01:36:31.000 --> 01:36:35.000
a front page, a page three, that the Chatham County Crusade for Voters,

01:36:35.000 --> 01:36:40.000
office where I had been arrested, where the Civil Rights Movement was in the office,

01:36:40.000 --> 01:36:45.000
apparently for a nominal rent, maybe a dollar or something,

01:36:45.000 --> 01:36:48.000
or a free of the International Union of Mine, Mill, and Smelter Workers,

01:36:48.000 --> 01:36:53.000
which had been thrown out of the, uh, CIO in 1947,

01:36:53.000 --> 01:36:57.000
during the days after the Taft-Hartley Act was passed,

