uh, as a Communist Control Union.

01:37:01.000 --> 01:37:06.000
And, I saw this, and wasn't sure,

01:37:06.000 --> 01:37:11.000
if I could trust my own judgment, but Aaron Buchsbaum also saw it

01:37:11.000 --> 01:37:15.000
with somewhat more independent eye, and both of us had the same reaction.

01:37:15.000 --> 01:37:20.000
And that is, it looked like the way this story out of Atlanta was,

01:37:20.000 --> 01:37:24.000
which was normally the Constitution's approach to civil rights papers.

01:37:24.000 --> 01:37:28.000
And the other hand, there's a great fear about the Communists being involved in the Civil Rights Movement,

01:37:28.000 --> 01:37:35.000
and they're also, the trajectory of the story was aimed at me.

01:37:35.000 --> 01:37:40.000
Was it just that I saw it, Aaron Buchsbaum saw it,

01:37:40.000 --> 01:37:43.000
independent of me, contacted my folks and said,

01:37:43.000 --> 01:37:45.000
I don't like the way this story is unfolding,

01:37:45.000 --> 01:37:49.000
because one day it passed, and two days it passed, so it was over.

01:37:49.000 --> 01:37:54.000
And the, the reaction of the Civil Rights people in the Chatham County was,

01:37:54.000 --> 01:37:58.000
well, we don't know about this Taff Tartley, or, you know, this,

01:37:58.000 --> 01:38:01.000
that was in the 40s, this is early 60s, and so on.

01:38:01.000 --> 01:38:03.000
And I think that is probably a true.

01:38:03.000 --> 01:38:06.000
But any of that, but here's this, who is this fellow,

01:38:06.000 --> 01:38:09.000
and he's coming in at Mississippi and all that,

01:38:09.000 --> 01:38:11.000
and you can't remember the things specifically said Mississippi,

